{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KQaUTXmnrHM85PEC5NKKKh","type":"tool_result","content":"A Spark cluster and data skew benchmark job have been deployed, but there are\nconfiguration issues that need to be fixed before the jobs can run successfully.\n\nYOUR TASK:\n1. Diagnose and fix the configuration bugs in the deployment\n2. Apply optimization strategies to fix the data skew problem\n3. Compare performance across different strategies\n\nPROBLEM DESCRIPTION:\n- Dataset: orders (large), products (small), customers (medium)\n- Join on product_id has severe data skew\n- 5 hot products (product_id 1-5) receive 50% of all orders\n- This causes some partitions to be 10x larger than others\n- Result: Slow query performance due to stragglers\n\nSTEP 1: DIAGNOSE AND FIX CLUSTER/JOB ISSUES\nThe initial deployment has bugs that prevent jobs from running.\nCheck the status and logs to identify and fix the issues.\n\n```bash\n# Check cluster and job status\nkubectl get pods -n spark-skew\nkubectl get jobs -n spark-skew\n\n# Check Spark master logs for startup issues\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l app=spark-master\n\n# Check baseline job logs for errors\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=baseline\n```\n\nSTEP 2: ONCE FIXED - OBSERVE THE BASELINE\n```bash\n# Check baseline job status\nkubectl get job spark-skew-baseline -n spark-skew\n\n# Watch baseline job logs - observe the skew ratio and slow performance\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=baseline -f\n```\n\nSTEP 3: APPLY BROADCAST JOIN OPTIMIZATION\n```bash\n# Apply the broadcast join job (may need fixes too)\nkubectl apply -f cases/spark/spark_data_skew/resource/skew-job-broadcast.yaml\n\n# Watch the broadcast job - should be faster!\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=broadcast -f\n```\n\nSTEP 4: APPLY AQE OPTIMIZATION\n```bash\n# Apply the AQE (Adaptive Query Execution) job\nkubectl apply -f cases/spark/spark_data_skew/resource/skew-job-aqe.yaml\n\n# Watch the AQE job - Spark auto-handles skew\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=aqe -f\n```\n\nSTEP 5: COMPARE RESULTS\n```bash\n# Check all jobs completed\nkubectl get jobs -n spark-skew\n\n# View all job logs to compare performance\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=baseline --tail=20\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=broadcast --tail=20\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=aqe --tail=20\n```\n\nSUCCESS CRITERIA:\n- All configuration bugs fixed\n- Baseline job completed successfully (shows slow performance)\n- At least ONE optimization strategy applied (broadcast or aqe)\n- Optimization shows performance improvement vs baseline\n- All applied jobs completed successfully","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0c18ae28-8a7a-42ed-b87c-d56c101b0e88","uuid":"6ebc7847-8a72-4beb-ab9c-63fb4f0bbcb7","timestamp":"2026-06-24T05:54:40.109Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"A Spark cluster and data skew benchmark job have been deployed, but there are\nconfiguration issues that need to be fixed before the jobs can run successfully.\n\nYOUR TASK:\n1. Diagnose and fix the configuration bugs in the deployment\n2. Apply optimization strategies to fix the data skew problem\n3. Compare performance across different strategies\n\nPROBLEM DESCRIPTION:\n- Dataset: orders (large), products (small), customers (medium)\n- Join on product_id has severe data skew\n- 5 hot products (product_id 1-5) receive 50% of all orders\n- This causes some partitions to be 10x larger than others\n- Result: Slow query performance due to stragglers\n\nSTEP 1: DIAGNOSE AND FIX CLUSTER/JOB ISSUES\nThe initial deployment has bugs that prevent jobs from running.\nCheck the status and logs to identify and fix the issues.\n\n```bash\n# Check cluster and job status\nkubectl get pods -n spark-skew\nkubectl get jobs -n spark-skew\n\n# Check Spark master logs for startup issues\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l app=spark-master\n\n# Check baseline job logs for errors\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=baseline\n```\n\nSTEP 2: ONCE FIXED - OBSERVE THE BASELINE\n```bash\n# Check baseline job status\nkubectl get job spark-skew-baseline -n spark-skew\n\n# Watch baseline job logs - observe the skew ratio and slow performance\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=baseline -f\n```\n\nSTEP 3: APPLY BROADCAST JOIN OPTIMIZATION\n```bash\n# Apply the broadcast join job (may need fixes too)\nkubectl apply -f cases/spark/spark_data_skew/resource/skew-job-broadcast.yaml\n\n# Watch the broadcast job - should be faster!\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=broadcast -f\n```\n\nSTEP 4: APPLY AQE OPTIMIZATION\n```bash\n# Apply the AQE (Adaptive Query Execution) job\nkubectl apply -f cases/spark/spark_data_skew/resource/skew-job-aqe.yaml\n\n# Watch the AQE job - Spark auto-handles skew\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=aqe -f\n```\n\nSTEP 5: COMPARE RESULTS\n```bash\n# Check all jobs completed\nkubectl get jobs -n spark-skew\n\n# View all job logs to compare performance\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=baseline --tail=20\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=broadcast --tail=20\nkubectl logs -n spark-skew -l strategy=aqe --tail=20\n```\n\nSUCCESS CRITERIA:\n- All configuration bugs fixed\n- Baseline job completed successfully (shows slow performance)\n- At least ONE optimization strategy applied (broadcast or aqe)\n- Optimization shows performance improvement vs baseline\n- All applied jobs completed successfully","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
