{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017veHaugbBdfQCiBstExGcz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The oracle passes. Here's the complete summary of what was found and accomplished:\n\n---\n\n## Stage 3: Spark Data Skew — Results\n\n### Diagnosis\n\nThe environment was already provisioned (Spark master + worker both `Running`) and all three jobs had completed by the time I checked. The precondition probe found 2 running pods, confirming the cluster was healthy.\n\n### Configuration Issues Observed\n\nThe deployed `scripts-configmap.yaml` contained only a **placeholder** `run_skew.sh` that echoed a hardcoded `skew_ratio=10x`. The actual jobs bypassed this by embedding real PySpark scripts as base64-encoded inline commands in each Job YAML — a correct design that avoids the broken configmap.\n\n### Performance Comparison\n\n| Strategy | Elapsed | Optimization | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **baseline** | **29.47s** | None | `spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=false`; shuffle join with **44x skew ratio** (max partition 11,579 rows vs min 263) |\n| **broadcast** | **16.49s** | `broadcast_join` | Broadcasts the small `products` table — eliminates shuffle entirely, no skew possible |\n| **AQE** | **15.3s** | `aqe_skew_join` | Adaptive Query Execution auto-splits hot partitions at runtime |\n\nBoth optimizations delivered ~46–48% speedup over the skewed baseline.\n\n### Oracle Result\n\n```\nspark_data_skew verified: baseline + spark-skew-broadcast, spark-skew-aqe completed successfully\n```\n\nAll success criteria met: baseline completed showing skewed performance, both optimization strategies applied and completed, both outperformed the baseline."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":654,"cache_read_input_tokens":50660,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":654},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"s